  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main hypothesis of this clinical trial is that the use of intra-articular tranexamic acid
      and the fibrin glue plus usual hemostasis will reduce at least a 25% the postoperative blood
      loss with respect to usual hemostasis in patients undergoing subcapital femoral fractures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
